    59	**Tone rules:**
    60	
    61	1. **No comparative judgment language.** Never "more sophisticated," "more mature," "stronger," "weaker," "where their thinking was sharper," "lacks," "fails to," etc.
    62	2. **Attribute approaches to context.** "KBM's approach reflects [their California sales motion / their relationship-led pipeline / their goal of consolidating activity]." "Pivot's approach reflects [their divisional structure / their MillerKnoll-Certified position / their in-house operations footprint]."
    63	3. **Recommendations are forward-looking.** "Operating from [Company]'s framework positions the merged company well because [context-based reasoning]." Not "[Company] got it right."
    64	4. **No advocacy or political commentary.** No "would do real damage to morale," "doesn't care strongly," "where their thinking was sharper." No internal-drafting commentary about which leadership team gets surprised.
    65	5. **No self-deprecating quotes from BRDs.** Even if a company described its own pain colorfully (e.g., KBM's "poo in, poo out"), don't surface those phrases in the unification doc. Reflecting them back to the team is unnecessary and risks landing wrong.
    66	6. **Both companies are credited.** Each section's "Recommendation summary" or "Net read" paragraph names what each company contributes to the merged-company outcome, framed positively for both.
    67	
    68	## Style and grammar
    69	
    70	- **Singular pronoun agreement** for "the company" — *it / its*, not *they / their*. ("Each company entered Orion implementation with established business processes shaped by how each operated at the time.")
    71	- **Comma after introductory clauses.** ("Originally framed around Construction Solutions, but explicitly broadened in the Feb 2026 review session...")
    72	- **Active where possible.** "We state it up front because" not "Stating it up front matters because."
    73	- **Em-dash (—) for parenthetical asides**, with spaces on either side.
    74	- **Section references** use § (U+00A7) — do not write "section" in body text when referencing.
    75	- **Em-dash, en-dash, hyphen** — em-dash for breaks, hyphen for compound words; avoid en-dash unless representing a range.
    76	
    77	## Per-area section template
    78	
    79	Verbatim from Chris-edited Doc Zero §6:
    80	
    81	```
    82	3.0X — [Process Area]
    83	  Decision density:    [Low / Medium / High + one-line headline]
    84	  Source coverage:     [What KBM and Pivot evidence is available]
    85	
    86	  3.0X.1  How each company approaches [process area] today
    87	  3.0X.2  Where the two companies align
    88	  3.0X.3  Where the two companies differ
