   111	
   112	**Decision for the leadership team.** [Explicit decision, with default recommendation]
   113	```
   114	
   115	For decisions with sub-parts (e.g., D-3 has 3a / 3b / 3c), use a decisions list:
   116	
   117	```
   118	**Decisions for the leadership team.**
   119	
   120	- (Na) [...] *Recommended default: yes.*
   121	- (Nb) [...] *Recommended default: confirm at session.*
   122	- (Nc) [...] *Recommended default: yes.*
   123	```
   124	
   125	## Decisions table format
   126	
   127	In §3.0X.6:
   128	
   129	```
   130	| # | Decision | Default | Reference |
   131	|---|---|---|---|
   132	| 1 | [Decision text] | Yes | D-1 |
   133	| 2a | [Decision text] | Yes | D-2a |
   134	| 2b | [Decision text] | Confirm at session | D-2b |
   135	```
   136	
   137	Always include a footer line:
   138	
   139	> N decisions: X with default-yes recommendations and Y requiring leadership-team input during the working session.
   140	
   141	Math must reconcile against the table.
   142	
   143	## Cross-area dependencies pattern
   144	
   145	Items decided in another area but surfacing here go in §3.0X.4 with this table:
   146	
   147	```
   148	| Dependency | Where it surfaced in [Area] | Where it's decided |
   149	|---|---|---|
   150	| **[Dependency name]** | [Source ref] | **[Other Area (§3.0X)]** — [one-line why it lives there] |
   151	```
   152	
   153	Do not duplicate the decision in both areas. Cross-reference only.
   154	
   155	## Source citation rules
   156	
   157	Every divergence cites:
   158	- KBM REQ IDs with file path and section number, e.g., `KBM REQ-016 (BRD_CRM_v1.0.md §5)`
   159	- Pivot REQ IDs with file path, e.g., `Pivot REQ-3.01.01 (CRM.md §3.01)`
