   521	## <a id="_Toc213923729"></a>3\.03 Work Order Management
   522	
   523	### <a id="_Toc213923730"></a>3\.03\.01 Your Business Requirements
   524	
   525	Pivot Interiors requires sophisticated work order management that streamlines creation, supports complex phased installations, and eliminates manual handoffs between systems\. Key requirements include:
   526	
   527	__REQ\-3\.03\.01:__ Streamlined work order creation from sales order lines
   528	
   529	__REQ\-3\.03\.02:__ Automated dashboard reminders when all purchase orders are acknowledged and ready for scheduling
   530	
   531	__REQ\-3\.03\.03:__ Custom groupings in smart table for purchase order organization
   532	
   533	__REQ\-3\.03\.04:__ Work order creation based on purchase order groups rather than line items
   534	
   535	__REQ\-3\.03\.05:__ Support for phased installations
   536	
   537	__REQ\-3\.03\.06:__ Multiple work order events for single work orders
   538	
   539	__REQ\-3\.03\.07:__ Elimination of manual file transfer and duplication across systems
   540	
   541	__REQ\-3\.03\.08:__ Coordination with installation managers for scheduling
   542	
   543	__REQ\-3\.03\.09:__ Automated notifications when work orders are scheduled
   544	
   545	### <a id="_Toc213923731"></a>3\.03\.02 Current State Process
   546	
   547	Current work order process involves multiple systems with significant manual handoffs and file duplication\. Project Coordinators and Project Managers create work orders in Workfront after coordinating with installation managers and clients, then work orders are manually transferred to IQ Coordinator for installation team processing\.
   548	
   549	__Process Flow:__
   550	
   551	- PC/PM reaches out to installation manager outside system to discuss availability for specific week
   552	- Installation manager confirms capacity and provides specific dates
   553	- PC/PM contacts client to confirm dates work for their schedule
   554	- After client approval, formal work order created in Workfront with scope, dates, and PO numbers
   555	- Work order submitted in Workfront to installation team
   556	- Installation team manually transfers text and information from Workfront to IQ Coordinator
   557	- Pick/pack lists printed from D365
   558	- Installation scheduled in IQ
   559	- Automated email sent to PC/PM when installation scheduled
   560	
   561	__Phasing Strategy:__
   562	
   563	Work orders are intentionally structured at the __purchase\-order level \(rather than individual line items\)__ to support complex, multi\-phase fulfillment models and optimize warehouse picking, staging, and outbound logistics\. Large\-scale installations follow a __sequenced delivery cadence__—for example, Day 1 \(~40% of materials\), Day 3 \(~40%\), and Day 5 \(final ~20%, including chairs and lighter components\)—requiring tightly coordinated inventory availability, labor resourcing, dock scheduling, and carrier management\.
   564	
   565	To enable these phased deployments, __custom PO groupings__ are leveraged to align materials to defined installation waves, providing greater control over shipment sequencing, site readiness, dependency management, and downstream field execution while reducing operational risk and re\-handling\.
   566	
   567	__Pain Points:__
   568	
   569	- Multiple manual handoffs between Workfront and IQ Coordinator
   570	- Significant file duplication across Workfront, quote requests, and IQ \(described as 'E\-waste'\)
   571	- Manual transfer process between systems is time\-consuming and error\-prone
   572	- No automated triggers indicating when scheduling readiness achieved
   573	- Current system doesn't optimize for purchase order grouping needed for warehouse efficiency
   574	
   575	### <a id="_Toc213923732"></a>3\.03\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
   576	
   577	NetSuite Orion streamlines work order management by eliminating system handoffs and supporting purchase order\-based work order creation\. The solution provides integrated workflow from sales order through work order creation and execution\.
   578	
   579	__Key Capabilities:__
   580	
   581	- Work orders created directly from sales order lines within single system
   582	- Dashboard reminders automatically trigger when all POs acknowledged
   583	- Custom groupings in smart table enable purchase order organization by phase
   584	- Mass selection and filtering capabilities by custom groups
   585	- Work orders created based on purchase order groups to avoid pallet splitting
   586	- Multiple work order events support phased installations
   587	- Files attached once and available across all related records
   588	- Coordination workflow supported through system notifications and assignments
   589	- Pick/pack lists generated directly from work orders
   590	
   591	### <a id="_Toc213923733"></a>3\.03\.04 Future State Process
