   787	
   788	**REQ-015: Enable soft scheduling with PM approval workflow (ADAPT)**
   789	
   790	Unlike hard scheduling (task is assigned, PM has no choice), soft scheduling requests PM approval. Someone can suggest a PM is available and propose scheduling them, but the PM must explicitly accept or decline. This approach respects PM autonomy, prevents scheduling conflicts, and maintains positive PM relationships. Similarly, contractors can be soft-scheduled for work, with approval required before commitment.
