   700	## <a id="_Toc213923735"></a>3\.04 Vendor Returns Management
   701	
   702	### <a id="_Toc213923736"></a>3\.04\.01 Your Business Requirements
   703	
   704	Pivot Interiors requires flexibility in vendor return management as most damaged products do not need to be returned to vendors\. Key requirements include:
   705	
   706	__REQ\-3\.04\.01:__ Decision point on implementing formal vendor return authorization \(VRA\) process
   707	
   708	__REQ\-3\.04\.02:__ Support for zero\-cost replacement product receiving
   709	
   710	__REQ\-3\.04\.03:__ Ability to track replacement products against original orders
   711	
   712	__REQ\-3\.04\.04:__ Vendor\-managed return logistics \(call tags and pickup arrangements\)
   713	
   714	__REQ\-3\.04\.05:__ Documentation and tracking for audit purposes
   715	
   716	### <a id="_Toc213923737"></a>3\.04\.02 Current State Process
   717	
   718	Vendor returns are relatively infrequent and handled informally\. Most damaged products are not returned as vendors typically send replacements at zero cost after reviewing damage photos\.
   719	
   720	__Process Flow:__
   721	
   722	- Issue identified with product \(damaged or wrong item\)
   723	- Vendor contacted with photos and documentation
   724	- Vendor evaluates need for physical return \(most often doesn't want product back\)
   725	- If return required, most often, the vendor provides call tag and arranges pickup at their expense\.  If was responsible for the error, client will pay  additional expenses\.
   726	- Product packaged with documentation and picked up by carrier
   727	- Replacement sent at zero cost on new PO line
   728	
   729	__Pain Points:__
   730	
   731	- Informal process with no systematic tracking
   732	- Need to decide if formal VRA process would be beneficial
   733	- Managing cost adjustments for replacements
   734	
   735	### <a id="_Toc213923738"></a>3\.04\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
   736	
   737	NetSuite Orion can support both formal and informal vendor return processes based on Pivot Interiors' decision\. The platform provides vendor return authorization functionality if needed while also supporting simple replacement tracking\.
   738	
   739	__Key Capabilities:__
   740	
   741	- Optional formal VRA process with approval workflows
   742	- Zero\-cost replacement product receiving support
   743	- Tracking of replacement products against original purchase orders\.  Will not create issues with invoicing
   744	- Documentation attachment for damage photos and correspondence
   745	- Audit trail for all return\-related activities
   746	
   747	### <a id="_Toc213923739"></a>3\.04\.04 Future State Process
   748	
