  1409	# SECTION 8: PUNCH LIST & FIELD OPERATIONS
  1410	
  1411	## 8.1 Your Business Requirements
  1412	
  1413	**REQ-024: Implement punch list functionality in Field Service app to replace PlanGrid (ACCOMMODATE)**
  1414	
  1415	KBM Hogue currently uses PlanGrid (third-party app) for punch list management in the field. Orion has built comprehensive punch list functionality directly into the Field Service app to eliminate this subscription cost. The Field Service app punch module includes all critical PlanGrid capabilities: creating punch items, attaching photos, documenting issues, and generating status reports. This is a significant custom Orion development that replaces an external tool.
  1416	
  1417	**REQ-025: Enable floor plan markup with location pinning for punch items (ACCOMMODATE)**
  1418	
  1419	The most critical feature of the Field Service app punch list is the ability to pin punch items to specific locations on floor plans. The problem this solves: "Four months later you get that punch item and you've done 15 jobs. You're like, yeah, I'll remember what room that goes into. And you don't. We all know the reality there." By pinning punch items to floor plan locations, months later any team member can look at the floor plan and instantly see exactly where each punch item is located.
  1420	
  1421	**REQ-026: Support offline mode for field app with sync capability (ALIGNS)**
  1422	
  1423	The Field Service app must work without internet connectivity because many installation sites have poor or no cell service. PMs need to download work order information in the morning, work offline throughout the day (creating punch items, taking photos, documenting work), and then sync when back online. This requires offline-capable database and sync engine.
  1424	
  1425	**REQ-027: Enable status report generation from field app (not just desktop) (ACCOMMODATE)**
  1426	
  1427	Currently, PlanGrid allows PMs to generate and email status reports directly from the iPad. The team initially hadn't planned to replicate this in NetSuite Field Service app, but Wendy needs this capability. Marcus agreed to add this functionality: PMs can generate status reports (showing daily progress, punch items, photos, etc.) directly from the tablet and email them to clients without returning to the office.
  1428	
  1429	**Requirements Classification:**
  1430	- Type: Functional - Field operations and issue management
  1431	- Priority: Must-Have (replaces paid tool, critical for field work)
  1432	- Users Impacted: PMs in field, clients receiving reports, operations team
  1433	- Business Impact: Eliminates PlanGrid subscription, improves field documentation, provides complete punch history
