  1469	## 8.3 Orion/NetSuite Solution
  1470	
  1471	Orion/NetSuite provides a comprehensive Field Service app that consolidates all field operations into a single, integrated platform. The punch list functionality within the Field Service app eliminates the need for external tools like PlanGrid while adding integration with work orders, projects, and inventory systems.
  1472	
  1473	**Punch List Core Capability:**
  1474	
  1475	The Field Service app punch module allows PMs to create punch items directly from their tablets or mobile phones during site visits. Each punch item includes:
  1476	- Photo evidence (camera interface captures images)
  1477	- Punch reason (what's wrong: damage, misalignment, missing, etc.)
  1478	- Issue type (punch list item vs. bill discrepancy vs. warehouse damage)
  1479	- Responsible party (who needs to fix it: contractor, KBM, client)
  1480	- Associated items (which products on the order relate to this punch)
  1481	- Status (open, in progress, resolved, deferred, etc.)
  1482	
  1483	**Floor Plan Location Pinning:**
  1484	
  1485	The most powerful feature is floor plan integration. Floor plans can be uploaded to the project (in PDF or image format), and punch items can be pinned directly to locations on the floor plan. This visual reference prevents the "I'll remember what room that was" problem. Months later, any team member can pull up the floor plan, see all punch items visually pinned to their exact locations, and instantly understand the scope of remaining work.
  1486	
  1487	**Offline Mode:**
  1488	
  1489	Critical for installations in buildings with no cell service. PMs log in during morning connectivity, downloading all work order events and floor plans. They then work offline throughout the day: creating punch items, taking photos, documenting work. When back online (or at end of day), the app automatically syncs all new punch items and photos back to the server. Sync includes conflict resolution—if the same punch item was modified on desktop during the day, sync intelligently merges changes.
  1490	
  1491	**Status Report Generation:**
  1492	
  1493	Rather than relying on PlanGrid to generate reports, the Field Service app includes reporting capability. PMs can generate status reports directly from the app, showing:
  1494	- Date and project
  1495	- Completed items (what was accomplished today)
  1496	- Punch items identified (what issues found)
  1497	- Photos and descriptions
  1498	- Next steps
  1499	- PM signature
  1500	
  1501	Reports can be generated in PDF format and emailed directly from the app to clients, providing immediate communication without returning to office.
  1502	
  1503	**Issue Type Flexibility:**
  1504	
  1505	NetSuite's generic "issue" concept is more flexible than PlanGrid's punch-only approach. Issues can be:
  1506	- Punch list items (post-installation defects)
  1507	- Bill discrepancies (price differences on invoice)
  1508	- Acknowledgement discrepancies (item variations)
  1509	- Warehouse damage (damage discovered at receiving)
  1510	- General notes (anything that's wrong)
  1511	
  1512	This flexibility allows consolidating multiple issue types into a single system rather than using separate tools.
  1513	
  1514	**Integration with Work Orders:**
  1515	
  1516	Punch items link directly to work order events. PM is assigned to a work order event, checks in, performs work, creates punch items. The punch items are directly associated with that work order, creating complete traceability of what was done and what issues remain.
  1517	
  1518	This approach has been successfully deployed across contract furniture dealers and represents best practice for field operations and punch management.
