735:### <a id="_Toc213923738"></a>3\.04\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
736:
737:NetSuite Orion can support both formal and informal vendor return processes based on Pivot Interiors' decision\. The platform provides vendor return authorization functionality if needed while also supporting simple replacement tracking\.
738:
739:__Key Capabilities:__
740:
741:- Optional formal VRA process with approval workflows
742:- Zero\-cost replacement product receiving support
743:- Tracking of replacement products against original purchase orders\.  Will not create issues with invoicing
744:- Documentation attachment for damage photos and correspondence
745:- Audit trail for all return\-related activities
746:
747:### <a id="_Toc213923739"></a>3\.04\.04 Future State Process
748:
749:Future state process will be determined based on Pivot Interiors' decision on formal VRA implementation\. Regardless of approach, system will track replacements against original orders with proper cost handling\.
750:
751:__If Formal VRA Process Adopted:__
752:
753:- Issue identified and documented in NetSuite with photos
754:- VRA created and submitted to vendor through system
755:- Vendor response tracked in system
756:- If physical return required, return authorization and tracking number recorded
757:- Replacement received at zero cost against original PO
758:- Complete audit trail maintained
759:
760:__If Informal Process Maintained:__
761:
762:- Issue documented in NetSuite with basic details
763:- Vendor coordination handled outside system
764:- Replacement received at zero cost with notation linking to original issue
